<br>
Pathing is also an important issue.  In FM the mobs all followed the same path to a spot where they would just walk back and forth while my pet beat it down.  You have to find these spots in the pathing.  There's a similar spot in Ill omen, by the lake, right in front of the pillars that go down to the underwater goblin fort thingy. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zikudeadscale>ZikuDeadscale</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#330000>(12/20/02 1:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfaqs.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: a must read for soloing enchanters</span><hr size=1> always haste your charmed pets, if you are wearing HP gear, not CHA gear like a sucker, you will be able to channel that stun, otherwise, go back to LOIO/OT/DL/Velks and group up with the rest of the people who dont know how to play this game. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=charmroxors>Charmroxors</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 97<br> <font color=#330000>(4/12/03 12:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfaqs.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: a must read for soloing enchanters</span><hr size=1> /bumping this old guide, seeing as a few had questions about charming below 60 and such.  <p>Charmroxors<br>
